ny serious sadhakas may not experience it.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Firs=\r\ntly, Kundalini rise is NOT an achievement. It is just A SMALL&gt; STEP in over=\r\ncoming one&#39;s current limited identity.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Let me give an analogy.=\r\n One\n wanting to move from one&#39;s small dilapidated house (this&gt; body-mind c=\r\nomplex) to a huge palace (realized Self) may first construct the palace ove=\r\nr time and move into it when it is COMPLETE. Alternately, if one occasional=\r\nly goes and stays in the palace still under construction (analogy for out o=\r\nf body experiences due to Kundalini rise), is it an achievement? In fact, i=\r\nt comes with risks. The former approach is safer and one loses nothing in i=\r\nt. Similarly, one can progress towards complete Self-realization without an=\r\ny out of body experiences. These are not my word&#39;s, but Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;=\r\ns words to Lord Rama.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Secondly, one does not get something wit=\r\nhout wanting it and putting sufficient effort towards it. One may have deep=\r\nly desired a Kundalini rise in a previous life and may have put enough effo=\r\nrt. As a result, one may be getting it now. But one may be unprepared (and =\r\nironically may not even want it!) when it comes in this life.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\nAs you\n do sadhana, try not to fancy too many specific&gt; desires. Nature has=\r\n a delay mechanism in granting your desires (because of constraints on what=\r\n Nature can give you right now, arising from YOUR&gt; OWN previous actions). S=\r\no Nature sometimes gives you what you want LATE, when you no longer want it=\r\n or want something else. For example, one may pray for great wealth one&#39;s w=\r\nhole life and be born as a rich but very sick man in next life. One may not=\r\n enjoy that wealth and pray whole life for health. In the life after that, =\r\none may be very healthy, but not have any knowledge or money. In another &gt; =\r\ncase, one may deeply desire to act in a famous film. One may be reborn &gt; as=\r\n a tiger or a dog and act in a famous film, but not really enjoy that &gt; exp=\r\nerience. Basically, people keep going in circles through various lives, alw=\r\nays &quot;seeking&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, coming bac=\r\nk to Kundalini, if one deeply desires an out of body experience given by a\n=\r\n rising Kundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from having it in=\r\n THIS life, one may be born in next life with this specific desire destined=\r\n to fructify (if there is enough karmik force behind it).&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0&gt; *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or painfu=\r\nl, if one is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachment.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; =\r\n&gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went to free it and it pan=\r\nicked so badly and started to shake violently. I went to save it from a cer=\r\ntain slow death and it was scared that I would kill it!&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;We are=\r\n like that chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap called this body-mind complex =\r\nand scared of being rescued from a certain slow death!&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;If our =\r\nideas about who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) are incorrect a=\r\nnd if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a complete realiza=\r\ntion of that at some stage involve stepping out of this body-mind\n complex,=\r\n without being scared?&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini=\r\n rise after most undesirable conditioning is overcome, is far better than&gt; =\r\nKundalini rise forced when some really undesirable conditioning is still le=\r\nft in one&#39;s system.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;When one transcends one problematic notion=\r\n about who one is and what one needs, another notion that lay buried deeper=\r\n in consciousness may spring to the surface and torment one. If one overcom=\r\nes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be another notion in one&#39;s body-mi=\r\nnd complex that one&#39;s awareness clings on to (e.g. a great doctor, a great =\r\nleader, a great scholar, a great saint etc). As an extreme example, if one =\r\nperson had a hidden deep desire to be a great soul who rescues the world, h=\r\ne may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y who will rescue the world now=\r\n. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!) deeply clings to any such not=\r\nion, it can cause havoc. The person may show some\n signs of progress and ye=\r\nt remain in ignorance and get stuck badly.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;An awakened Kundali=\r\nni in a system with undesirable conditioning may accentuate one&#39;s weaknesse=\r\ns and wrong notions heavily and cause serious psychiatric and spiritual pro=\r\nblems.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;The best approach I recomm=\r\nend is to NOT think in terms of Kundalini and its rise. Just do sadhana, ov=\r\nercome your&gt; weaknesses and improve your detachment over time. Again, I wan=\r\nt to emphasize that detachment is not disgust or distaste for life/things/p=\r\neople around you. Disgust is the other side of coin of attachment. It is a =\r\nnegative attachment.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Don&#39;t worry about &gt; whether your Kund=\r\nalini rises or not. Worry about whether you are able to resist 6 internal e=\r\nnemies (shadripus) and 8 bondages (ashta pashas) or &gt; not. If your ability =\r\nto resist them is increasing, you are making progress. EVEN IF your Kundali=\r\nni is fast asleep, you are still making\n progress. When you completely over=\r\ncome them, Kundalini (your self-awareness) &gt; will automatically ascend to t=\r\nhe top and meet Her Lord (true Self).&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;One word on surrendering to a personal deity. Though true surrender =\r\nis helpful, most people do not have it. They simply do business with god. T=\r\nhough people may be offended by my words, this is the plain and bare fact.&gt;=\r\n &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;&quot;I want X, I will pray to you and please give it to me&quot;, &quot;I am=\r\n scared of Kundalini rise, I will pray to you and please protect me&quot; - all =\r\nthis is just a business deal. There is something you want and you ask god f=\r\nor it. True surrender has no place for agendas, desires, demands or expecta=\r\ntions. True surrender is losing oneself in one&#39;s fascination for the qualit=\r\nies of Lord. True surrender is accepting anything Lord throws one&#39;s way (wh=\r\nether it is pleasurable or highly painful) as Lord&#39;s prasad and accepting i=\r\nt gratefully. True surrender\n is thinking of Lord with fascination and plea=\r\nsure, even in the face of (and during) Death.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;If one without t=\r\nrue surrender and with many desires and wrong notions experiences a Kundali=\r\nni rise, one may still be trapped, despite thinking of a personal god. It i=\r\ns not that god does not want to &quot;protect&quot; one as said below. It is not abou=\r\nt protecting or endangering. If you go back to my &quot;chipmunk glued to mouse =\r\ntrap&quot; example above, I was trying to protect it, but it was scared. Similar=\r\nly, one&#39;s conditioning makes one *run away* from God&#39;s&gt; protection! God&#39;s p=\r\nrotection may seem to a conditioned mind like grave danger that one should =\r\nrun away from!&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Whether through t=\r\nhe path of wisdom or surrender, develop dispassion and detachment. Realize =\r\nthat all this is temporary and can be taken away anytime. Enjoy it while yo=\r\nu have and keep doing your best, but be prepared to lose everything anytime=\r\n. Only detachment\n and a very light mental conditioning (very light desires=\r\n, dislikes etc) can protect one as one&#39;s Kundalini rises to meet True Self.=\r\n Heavy conditioning and impurities in one&#39;s nadis will distract rising Kund=\r\nalini (self-awareness) and stop Her from meeting True Self.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Th=\r\ne real key is how light your conditioning is.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Best regards,&gt; &gt;=\r\n&gt;Narasimha&gt; &gt;&gt;--------&gt; &gt;&gt;Astrology & Spirituality Resources: http://www.ve=\r\ndicastrologer.org/&gt; &gt;&gt;--------&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;__________________=\r\n______________&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; From: Leela Sastry &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;To: &quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yaho=\r\nogroups.com&quot; mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;Sent: Thursday, Fe=\r\nbruary 28, 2013 6:05 AM&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Kundalini syndrome&gt;=\r\n &gt;&gt;&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0 &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0YES=C2=A0 SIR=C2=A0 , perfectly correct=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 ,=C2=A0but intense bhakthi and saranagathi=C2=A0 makes the ishtad=\r\nevatha to stand by the sadhaka and remove most of the hurdles .=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\nAll the so called dhyanamargas with out any personal deity and\n manthra all=\r\now the other entities to enter in to the inner planes who play havoc with t=\r\nhe=C2=A0 psyche .=C2=A0 Once we are under the protection of=C2=A0 a mahadev=\r\natha ,all the other=C2=A0 disturbance