gt;Secondly, many people who have Kundalini r=\r\nise are brought up with the concept of japa. Japa which deals with the Air =\r\nelement which is unstable anyway can cause serious instability in these peo=\r\nple.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;Some&nbsp;of the&nbsp;people who have Kundalini &quot;rises&quot; m=\r\nay be people who may feel that they haven&#39;t done a single worthwhile thing =\r\nin their lives and think that the faking of Kundalini rises may help them g=\r\net some esteem in the eye of the general public.&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;Coming =\r\nto the specific problem:In general, for any doctor, the separation of the t=\r\nrue from the false\n claims must precede any attempt at helping the patient.=\r\n A true Kundalini rise needs niyama to finish Vata. Vata tends to like irre=\r\ngularity, in food habits, sleeping habits, sexual matters, travel.&nbsp;&lt;WB=\r\nR&gt;&gt; &gt;To finish Vata, all&nbsp;that must be regimentalised, then appro=\r\npriate herbs used. Control of Apana is essential as is Bramhacharya. Applic=\r\nation of oils to the body to totally calm Vata may be useful. I suppose eve=\r\nn Shiro basti in difficult real cases may be useful.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;Then inst=\r\nitute small&nbsp;Homas to MahaGanapati and the nava grahas to be performed =\r\nby the patient. That should really improve matters, as Ganesha is The Lord =\r\nof the Muladhara.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;The whole process may be chalked out over on=\r\ne-two years.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;In pure non real cases, just psychotherapy may be=\r\n sufficient.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;Jai Shree Rama&lt;WBR&gt;&g=\r\nt; &gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;Jai Shree Rama&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &g=\r\nt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt;\n &gt;On Friday, March 1, 2013, Narasimha P.V.R. Rao wrote:&lt;WBR&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;Namaste friends,&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &g=\r\nt;&gt;Someone with psychiatric problems may expereience what sounds like a =\r\nKundalini rise, but it may or may not be one.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&=\r\ngt; &gt;&gt;It must be conceded though that Kundalini spontaneously rising =\r\nthrough various nadis without one having gone through proper preparation in=\r\n this life (i.e. fine-tuning of one&#39;s attitude and development of detachmen=\r\nt) CAN create havoc!&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;One may wonde=\r\nr how Kundalini may spontaneously rise in a layman with no sadhana, while m=\r\nany serious sadhakas may not experience it.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt=\r\n; &gt;&gt;Firstly, Kundalini rise is NOT an achievement. It is just A SMALL=\r\n&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; STEP in overcoming one&#39;s current limited identity.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&=\r\ngt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Let me give an analogy. One wanting to move from=\r\n\n one&#39;s small dilapidated house (this&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; body-mind complex) to a huge=\r\n palace (realized Self) may first construct the palace over time and move i=\r\nnto it when it is COMPLETE. Alternately, if one occasionally goes and stays=\r\n in the palace still under construction (analogy for out of body experience=\r\ns due to Kundalini rise), is it an achievement? In fact, it comes with risk=\r\ns. The former approach is safer and one loses nothing in it. Similarly, one=\r\n can progress towards complete Self-realization without any out of body exp=\r\neriences. These are not my word&#39;s, but Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s words to Lord R=\r\nama.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Secondly, one does not get so=\r\nmething without wanting it and putting sufficient effort towards it. One ma=\r\ny have deeply desired a Kundalini rise in a previous life and may have put =\r\nenough effort. As a result, one may be getting it now. But one may be unpre=\r\npared (and ironically may not even want it!) when it comes in this\n life.&lt;W=\r\nBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;As you do sadhana, try not to fancy=\r\n too many specific&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; desires. Nature has a delay mechanism in granti=\r\nng your desires (because of constraints on what Nature can give you right n=\r\now, arising from YOUR&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; OWN previous actions). So Nature sometimes g=\r\nives you what you want LATE, when you no longer want it or want something e=\r\nlse. For example, one may pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole life and be bor=\r\nn as a rich but very sick man in next life. One may not enjoy that wealth a=\r\nnd pray whole life for health. In the life after that, one may be very heal=\r\nthy, but not have any knowledge or money. In another &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; case, one ma=\r\ny deeply desire to act in a famous film. One may be reborn &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; as a t=\r\niger or a dog and act in a famous film, but not really enjoy that &lt;WBR&gt;&gt;=\r\n experience. Basically, people keep going in circles through various lives,=\r\n always &quot;seeking&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt;\n &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WB=\r\nR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kundalini, if one deeply desires an o=\r\nut of body experience given by a rising Kundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas=\r\n constrain one from having it in THIS life, one may be born in next life wi=\r\nth this specific desire destined to fructify (if there is enough karmik for=\r\nce behind it).&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&g=\r\nt; *&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessa=\r\nrily scary or painful, if one is well-prepared in terms of attitude and det=\r\nachment.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glu=\r\ned to a mouse trap. I went to free it and it panicked so badly and started =\r\nto shake violently. I went to save it from a certain slow death and it was =\r\nscared that I would kill it!&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;We ar=\r\ne like that chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap\n called this body-mind comple=\r\nx and scared of being rescued from a certain slow death!&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&=\r\nnbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;If our ideas about who we are (viz this current body=\r\n-mind complex) are incorrect and if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras=\r\n say, won&#39;t a complete realization of that at some stage involve stepping o=\r\nut of this body-mind complex, without being scared?&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;=\r\n&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;K=\r\nundalini rise after most undesirable conditioning is overcome, is far bette=\r\nr than&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; Kundalini rise forced when some really undesirable conditio=\r\nning is still left in one&#39;s system.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&g=\r\nt;When one transcends one problematic notion about who one is and what one =\r\nneeds, another notion that lay buried deeper in consciousness may spring to=\r\n the surface and torment one. If one\n overcomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;,=\r\n there may be another notion in one&#39;s body-mind complex that one&#39;s awarenes=\r\ns clings on to (e.g. a great doctor, a great leader, a great scholar, a gre=\r\nat saint etc). As an extreme example, if one person had a hidden deep desir=\r\ne to be a great soul who rescues the world, he may fancy that he is a re-in=\r\ncarnated X or Y who will rescue the world now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i=\r\n.e. Kundalini!) deeply clings to any such notion, it can cause havoc. The p=\r\nerson may show some signs of progress and yet remain in ignorance and get s=\r\ntuck badly.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;An awakened Kundalini =\r\nin a system with undesirable conditioning may accentuate one&#39;s weaknesses a=\r\nnd wrong notions heavily and cause serious psychiatric and spiritual proble=\r\nms.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&g=\r\nt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;The\n best approach I recommend is to NOT think in=\r\n terms of Kundalini and its rise. Just do sadhana, overcome your&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; w=\r\neaknesses and improve your detachment over time. Again, I want to emphasize=\r\n that detachment is not disgust or distaste for life/things/people around y=\r\nou. Disgust is the other side of coin of attachment. It is a negative attac=\r\nhment.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Don&#39;t wor=\r\nry about &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; whether your Kundalini rises or not. Worry about whether=\r\n you are able to resist 6 internal enemies (shadripus) and 8 bondages (asht=\r\na pashas) or &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; not. If your ability to resist them is increasing, y=\r\nou are making progress. EVEN IF your Kundalini is fast asleep, you are stil=\r\nl making progress. When you completely overcome them, Kundalini (your self-=\r\nawareness) &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; will automatically ascend to the top and meet Her Lord=\r\n (true Self).&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=\r\nnbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;WBR&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;One word on surrendering to a personal=\r\n deity. Though true surrender is helpful, most people do not have it. They =\r\nsimply do business with god. Though people may be offended by my words, thi=\r\ns is the plain and bare fact.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&quot;I w=\r\nant X, I will pray to you and please give it to me&quot;, &quot;I am scared of Kundal=\r\nini rise, I will pray to you and please protect me&quot; - all this is just a bu=\r\nsiness deal. There is something you want and you ask god for it. True surre=\r\nnder has no place for agendas, desires, demands or expectations. True surre=\r\nnder is losing oneself in one&#39;s fascination for the qualities of Lord. True=\r\n surrender is accepting anything Lord throws one&#39;s way (whether it is pleas=\r\nurable or highly painful) as Lord&#39;s prasad and accepting it gratefully. Tru=\r\ne surrender is thinking of Lord with fascination and pleasure, even in the =\r\nface of (and\n during) Death.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;If on=\r\ne without true surrender and with many desires and wrong notions experience=\r\ns a Kundalini rise, one may still be trapped, despite thinking of a persona=\r\nl god. It is not that god does not want to &quot;protect&quot; one as said below. It =\r\nis not about protecting or endangering. If you go back to my &quot;chipmunk glue=\r\nd to mouse trap&quot; example above, I was trying to protect it, but it was scar=\r\ned. Similarly, one&#39;s conditioning makes one *run away* from God&#39;s&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; =\r\nprotection! God&#39;s protection may seem to a conditioned mind like grave dang=\r\ner that one should run away from!&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Whether through the=\r\n path of wisdom or surrender, develop dispassion and detachment. Realize th=\r\nat all this is temporary and can be taken away anytime. Enjoy it while you =\r\nhave\n and keep doing your best, but be prepared to lose everything anytime.=\r\n Only detachment and a very light mental conditioning (very light desires, =\r\ndislikes etc) can protect one as one&#39;s Kundalini rises to meet True Self. H=\r\neavy conditioning and impurities in one&#39;s nadis will distract rising Kundal=\r\nini (self-awareness) and stop Her from meeting True Self.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;The real key is how light your conditioning is.&lt;WBR=\r\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Best regards,&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Narasi=\r\nmha&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;--------&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Astrology &amp; Spirituality=\r\n Resources: &lt;A href=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot; rel=3Dnofollow targ=\r\net=3D_blank&gt;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&lt;/A&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;--------&lt;W=\r\nBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt=\r\n;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;________________________________&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&g=\r\nt; From: Leela Sastry &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;To: &quot;&lt;A\n href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-w=\r\nisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=3D_blank ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:v=\r\nedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&lt;/A&gt;&quot; &lt;=\r\nA href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=3D_b=\r\nlank ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;mailto:vedic-wisdom%=\r\n40yahoogroups.com&lt;/A&gt;&gt; &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;Sent: Thursday, February 28=\r\n, 2013 6:05 AM&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Kundalini s=\r\nyndrome&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&=\r\nnbsp; &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&nbsp;YES&nbsp; SIR&nbsp; , perfectly correct&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp; ,&nbsp;but intense bhakthi and saranagathi&nbsp; makes the ishta=\r\ndevatha to stand by the sadhaka and remove most of the hurdles .&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;All the so called dhyanamargas with out any personal deity and manthra all=\r\now the other entities to enter in to the inner planes who play havoc with t=\r\nhe&nbsp; psyche .&nbsp; Once we are under the protection\n of&nbsp; a mahade=\r\nvatha ,all the other&nbsp; disturbances will definitely&nbsp; be wipe